			<div style="height:10px"></div>   <p class="postmeta">Posted by
    <a href="http://www.mizwhiz.com/author/admin" title="Posts by iYogi Technical Services" rel="author">iYogi Technical Services</a>    on
    Jul 14th, 2011,
   1,502 views    //
    <a href="http://www.mizwhiz.com/gadgets/apps-to-stop-you-from-texting-prevent-accidents-while-you-are-driving.html#comments" class="comments-link"  title="Comment on Apps To Stop You From Texting &amp; Prevent Accidents While You Are Driving">1 Comment</a>  </p>
  
  <div class="entry">
    <div class='rpuRepostUsButtonWrap' style='position:relative;float:right;padding-left:20px;'><a class='rpuRepostUsButton' href='https://secure.repost.us/syndicate/create?url=http://www.mizwhiz.com/gadgets/apps-to-stop-you-from-texting-prevent-accidents-while-you-are-driving.html'><img style='vertical-align:middle;' src='http://www.mizwhiz.com/wp-content/plugins/repostus/repostus_bttn_lng_repost.png'/></a></div>

<p><a href="http://mizwhiz.com/wp-content/uploads/multi-trigger2.png"><img class="alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-2551" title="multi-trigger2" src="http://mizwhiz.com/wp-content/uploads/multi-trigger2-150x150.png" alt="" width="150" height="150" /></a></p>
<p>Many a times, you must be fiddling with your mobile phones while driving home. Texting from your cell while driving car phone could put you, pedestrians or other cars in danger and may end up in a fatal road accident. Even knowing the severity of such situations, you may not avoid texting or calling from your cell phone on urgent situations such as, if you have a sick baby at home to be rushed to hospital, communicating to an elder person on emergency etc. To avoid the risks of road accidents while you type and send text messages, here are some apps that give great alternatives to fiddling with the buttons or the touchscreen of your cell phone so that you can keep your eyes on the road and do multitasking, at the same time:</p>
<p><strong>Dial-In Service</strong></p>
<p>One of the major types of apps to prevent you from being diverted is a speech-to-text or text-to-speech application. You need to subscribe for this Dial-in service. Once you take the subscription, this service will read your mails, even you can voice reply messages you want to send. As you can hear and voice your messages using this voice command based service, your hands will be free to use steering your car.</p>
<p><strong>Cell phone apps</strong></p>
<p>There are some apps that can disable most of your mobile phone’s functions. TextArrest, ZoomSafer are most popular apps of this kind as these will aptly detects while you are driving. These apps use GPS technology to measure the speed at which you are driving to deactivate many functions which could shift your attention once you reach at the pre-set speed. These apps come with ‘emergency override and passenger-usage exceptions’, online mobile phone use monitoring.</p>
<p><strong>Combination of tools hardware and apps</strong></p>
<p>If you do not want to rely on GPS based speed measuring and car usage technology, get this small module attached to your car at parts such as the OBD (what you call on-board diagnostics) module or emergency brake. As the module will be activated by your car usage, a signal will deactivate your phone automatically. There are some other tools that utilizes Bluetooth module to and enables voice based commands and text-to-speech options.
