	<li class="cat-item cat-item-56"><a href="http://www.mizwhiz.com/iyogi-fraud-protection" title="View all posts filed under iYogi Fraud Protection Alerts">iYogi Fraud Protection Alerts</a>
</li>
	<li class="cat-item cat-item-57"><a href="http://www.mizwhiz.com/iyogi-scam-alerts" title="Let’s face it-the Internet is both a boon and a  bane. Apart from the good that it has done, the Internet has also given birth  to cybercrime, something that has been on a continuous upswing. The people  orchestrating the devious scams that are overflowing the Internet are difficult  to track down because the Internet at its very core is an open platform that  has one loophole too many. Internet schemes are an unavoidable consequence of it  and though they cannot be erased completely, there are proven ways that can be  used to minimize their effect. The ‘iYogi  Scam Alerts’ are designed to  educate users about the different methods users can adopt to keep themselves  safe from Internet scams and frauds. They are basically aimed at spreading  awareness about the latest and most prevalent scams and how they can be dealt  with. 

  The way in which Internet scams are developing with  newer and deadlier versions of prototypes making their appearance ever so  frequently, it is mandatory that there is a logical scheme in place to rein  them in. There are major regulatory bodies that keep track of what is happening  in the world of Internet scams and they keep issuing warnings and guides for  the Internet community. But despite that, thousands are duped off their money  and many lose important personal information like credit card details, bank  information, and similar other sensitive info. Nowadays, almost everybody has  heard of such cons as the Nigerian 419 scams, online dating scams, identity  theft, etc. ‘iYogi Scam Alerts’ spread awareness Internet users about these  scams. Written in a simple easy-to-understand language and accessible to all,  ‘iYogi Scam Alerts’ educate users on staying safe online and what precautions  to take while surfing the web.

  As an educational tool, ‘iYogi Scam Alerts’ provide useful  guidelines for people who spend long hours on the Internet and engage in online  activities such as paying bills, downloading data, or even looking for romance.  Online scams normally target users who are greenhorns and don’t follow safe  surfing habits. The extent to which Internet scams can cause emotional trauma  is terrifying with many reports of psychological damage. Then there are people  whose businesses are wrecked to levels from where they cannot be restored. The  list is endless and if the trend is allowed to continue, the Internet will no  longer remain a source of pride but a scourge that traps and takes people for a  ride. The ‘iYogi Scam Alerts’ see to it that nothing of the sort happens and it  is you who boss around the scammers. The ‘iYogi Scam Alerts’ also deals with  the aftermath of a scam incident and how you must respond. 

  Whatever you do to keep Internet scams and frauds at  a safe distance, it finally boils down to using common sense and practicing  safe surfing habits when online. 
">iYogi Scam Alerts</a>
